name: A-League
summary: Various news articles highlight key events and developments in various sports leagues: In the A-League Women, there is concern over the loss of talented players due to insufficient pay and part-time competition. The A-League Men welcomes an all-female referee team for the first time. The Sioux Falls Surges make their mark in the United States Hockey League. FIBA Asia 2024 showcases exceptional performances. The CASS Huskies dominate in the Sault Ste. Marie High School Boys Hockey League. The Puerto Rico Double-A League 2025 is set to begin in March. The English Premier League reviews memorable escapes from relegation. The Friends of Football podcast analyzes Round 10 of the men's A-League. Lastly, the Hockey News reports on a controversial incident in a Wild game involving Zachary L'Heureux's slew-foot on Jared Spurgeon.

name: College Football
summary: The College Football Playoff quarterfinal games are set, with ESPN presenting the MegaCast on December 31st to January 1st. The NCAA website provides the schedule, rankings, and scores for the bracket. USA Today offers updates on the results, schedules, and how to watch the games. Amidst the excitement, Awful Announcing reports that the Playoff is considering changes to its seeding process. CBS Sports provides picks, schedules, and predictions for the quarterfinal bowl games. Forbes argues that the Playoff is perfect as it is. Yahoo Sports offers a viewer's guide to the new format. Sporting News also provides picks and predictions for the 2025 CFP quarterfinals. The article concludes with the news that Penn State has advanced to the semifinals after defeating Boise State.
